"Yes, sir. They should already be on their way now; we gave them time to pack food from the mess hall." At exactly 05:00, Exodus assembled at the vehicle depot. Captain Xiao stood on a box and began to speak.
"We will head to the I-131 frontline base 50 miles outside of Ianlos City. We will support the ongoing siege operation and then attack Ianlos City to clear out the rebels. We will use this as our base of operations and advance into the mountains." Captain Xiao explained. "Take your squad and prepare to depart."
The squad dispersed, with each squad taking a tank under the leadership of their squad leader. Colen climbed onto a tank at the front of the convoy, sitting with Nimich, Cres, and two new recruits. Colen remembered they had arrived just a few days ago, but he didn't know them well. He sat on the edge of the tank, legs hanging down, adjusting his backpack and radio equipment, and connecting it to his headphones and throat microphone.
"Hey, Colen, does Harris still have Snowball?" Nimich asked after they had settled in.
"You mean the chicken he stole?" Colen recalled the scene from that morning when they had stolen a chicken from the farm. "Yes, I'm sure of it."
Colen looked at another tank and saw Harris and his squad. He caught a glimpse of a small chicken wandering around behind Harris's backpack.
"Yes, he's still keeping that chicken." Colen answered, just as the tank's turret hatch clanged open and the crew commander appeared before them.
"All tanks are underway." The crew commander spoke calmly and clearly into his headset. The armored platoon's tanks and Stryker vehicles roared to life and began moving forward. Colen's Krone tank released the brake and moved forward, joining the formation. The tanks formed a wedge formation as they crossed the Itania plain. Winter blizzards had frozen the wetlands and forests, but mud still remained.
About an hour later, a new recruit (Colen remembered his name was Olsen) spoke up, "Lieutenant, have you been on the front lines since the war started?"
"Yes, I've been here since the Firestorm operation began," Colen replied. "We thought the fighting would end within a few weeks, but... we underestimated them."
"That's not just underestimating." Nimich joined the conversation. "Their weapons and numbers were beyond our expectations. They shot down the UFS Revenant in the first two weeks and the Erebus last month. Damn, we should have seen it on the way."
"Well, I'll fight bravely for the Federation," Olsen said firmly. "I won't be intimidated by those terrorists."
"You say that now, but from what I've seen, most new recruits who just came of age get so scared by the sound of gunfire that they wet themselves."
"Let's see about that," Colen laughed. Olsen said nothing more.
"Exodus Deputy Commander! Exodus Commander!" Colen's radio equipment called out. "We detected a heat signal at 20 degrees to our right, 350 yards away."
Colen climbed onto the tank and put on his optical goggles. After switching to thermal imaging mode, he saw a thermal signal in the distance.
"Yes, I see them," Colen said into his throat microphone.
"Are they enemies?" asked another new recruit, Natalie.
"Can't tell yet," Colen said, opening the microphone. "Exodus squad, don't fire unless attacked. Just draw them out first."
As they got closer, the faint thermal signal transformed from a blurred spot into a clearer outline. One of them ran to somewhere, picked up something, and then ran back to the hill ridge. Then, they all crouched down and took up firing positions.
"We've encountered enemies!" Captain Xiao shouted over the radio when a red tracer fired from the ridge. Bullets pinged off the tank's side, and the assault队员们 leaped down from the tanks, taking cover behind them. A anti-tank missile screamed toward them, crashing into the ground behind the tank formation, and shrapnel hit one of the tanks. Another missile struck the side of a Stryker vehicle (APS-Cerberus) and exploded. After the ammunition殉爆, the crew members of the vehicle crawled out, seeking cover.
"Iron 1-2 and 1-3, 25 degrees to the right, 300 yards. Fire!" The tank platoon leader shouted over the radio. The main guns of Iron 1-2 and 1-3 fired, launching shells toward the ridge, which exploded, sending dirt and碎石 flying into the air.
"Deploy sentry robots!" Knox shouted, as he was observing the ridge with a telescope. The back door of a "Hellhound" opened, and a soldier emerged without carrying any weapons, wearing special headphones. He shouted loudly into a square microphone, and two "sentry" robots emerged. Their slender metal arms and legs moved forward, and they ran quickly. The robots were equipped with weapons, but they were all attached to their backs.
"Kill or capture?" Cres asked while observing.
"It looks like they want to capture the live one," Colen guessed, watching as the two sentry robots disappeared into the ashes and smoke. Screaming and gunfire echoed from the ridge, but it quickly calmed down. After a while, the two sentry robots returned, dragging a person with their boots leaving a trail in the mud. Upon reaching the safe area, the robots threw the prisoner to the ground, where he crashed hard onto the muddy and snowy ground, moaning in pain.
He struggled to stand up, and Captain Xiao walked over. Captain Xiao turned to one of the sentry robots. "How many people?"
"Three deaths, sir." The sentry robot replied. "The rest have fled on foot."
Captain Xiao nodded, then turned to Colen and Cres, who were standing nearby. "Can you two take this person away?"
